featured_reviews.review_id: Though I am giving it a 5 rating but the present condition of this monument is so bad that one would not give any. I give it because even after being in such a deteorated condition this building will leave you awestruck by all means. Built by Miyan Makka who was a tailor of the second King of Awadh (Oudh) King Naseeruddin Haider. It came into existence for the purpose of Azadari (Muharram practices) but now  is  home to a multiple under privileged families. The detailed story of how this magnificent Imambada came into existence is not by a simple tailor but somebody who had an intricate sense of fashion and design is very interesting. There is a mosque just opposite to this and on the left hand side there is  an elevated monument called Qadam Rasool. All of these are religious places with a government sign board. The place is around 80 away kms from Lucknow.
